==============================
@Binds ‚Äî HILT INTERNAL RULES
==============================

üß† WHAT HILT READS (IMPORTANT)

Hilt DOES NOT execute the method.
Hilt ONLY reads the method signature.

FROM THE METHOD SIGNATURE:
--------------------------------
RETURN TYPE  ‚Üí Adder
PARAM TYPE   ‚Üí SimpleAdder

Hilt builds this mapping rule:
--------------------------------
Adder ‚Üê SimpleAdder


==============================
REQUIRED RULES FOR @Binds
(MUST MEMORIZE)
==============================

1Ô∏è‚É£ INTERFACE IS COMPULSORY
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ @Binds works ONLY with interface or abstract return types
‚Ä¢ Concrete class as return type ‚Üí ‚ùå NOT ALLOWED

Reason:
@Binds is for mapping abstractions, not creating objects


2Ô∏è‚É£ @Inject CONSTRUCTOR IS COMPULSORY
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ The implementation (SimpleAdder) MUST have @Inject constructor
‚Ä¢ Hilt must know HOW to create the implementation
‚Ä¢ Without @Inject constructor ‚Üí ‚ùå Compile-time error

Reason:
@Binds does NOT create objects
It only selects which implementation to use


3Ô∏è‚É£ MODULE MUST BE ABSTRACT
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ @Binds methods have no body
‚Ä¢ Abstract methods require abstract class
‚Ä¢ Object / concrete class ‚Üí ‚ùå NOT ALLOWED


4Ô∏è‚É£ METHOD MUST BE ABSTRACT
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ No method body { }
‚Ä¢ No return statement
‚Ä¢ No logic
‚Ä¢ Hilt NEVER executes this method

Reason:
This is a rule declaration, not executable code


5Ô∏è‚É£ NO CREATION LOGIC ALLOWED
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Cannot use:
  - new
  - return
  - if / when
  - parameters logic

‚Ä¢ Only TYPE MAPPING is allowed

Reason:
Creation responsibility belongs to @Inject constructor


==============================
WHEN TO USE @Binds
==============================

Use @Binds WHEN:
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ You have an interface
‚Ä¢ You own the implementation
‚Ä¢ Implementation has @Inject constructor
‚Ä¢ No custom creation logic needed
‚Ä¢ You want compile-time efficiency


==============================
WHEN NOT TO USE @Binds
==============================

Do NOT use @Binds WHEN:
--------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Object creation requires logic
‚Ä¢ Third-party class
‚Ä¢ No @Inject constructor possible
‚Ä¢ You need conditional creation

Use @Provides instead


==============================
FINAL MEMORY HOOK (GOLDEN)
==============================

@Inject constructor ‚Üí HOW to create
@Binds              ‚Üí WHICH implementation
@Inject field       ‚Üí WHAT is required


==============================
ONE-LINE SUMMARY
==============================

@Binds does NOT create objects.
@Binds only maps:
--------------------------------
Interface  ‚Üí  Implementation
